                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 10, Acting Secretary <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">Webb</persName> reported
                    on the progress of the Council of Foreign Ministers at a meeting of the Cabinet.
                    He noted that there was “… no real indication that the Russians were prepared to
                    do the things necessary to reach an understanding even with respect to the
                    unification of Berlin.” <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">Webb</persName>’s record of
                    this meeting and of another meeting the same day with President Truman at which
                    he left a status report on the Council of Foreign Ministers, neither printed,
                    are in file 740.00119 Council/6–1049.</p>
            </div>
